NAME
	comp-list (display) - list the compositions in a directory as clickable rows that load the chosen one via the Matrix ctl file

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	<mount>		a directory of composition files (normally
			/lib/matrix/compositions); each entry's first
			comment line is shown as its description.

WRITES
	/mnt/matrix/ctl	"load <name>" when a row is clicked.

DESCRIPTION
	The module behind the default picker composition
	(/lib/matrix/compositions/picker).  It enumerates the mount
	directory, skips the picker composition itself, and renders one
	row per composition: name on the left, the description scraped
	from the file's leading comment on the right.  A click writes
	"load <name>" to the Matrix control file, replacing the current
	composition in place.  Because the picker is itself an ordinary
	crystallisation wired to this module, users and agents can edit
	or replace it like any other composition.

SEE ALSO
	/lib/matrix/compositions/picker (the crystallisation using this)
	docs/matrix-architecture.md (the ctl load verb)
